<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>The Influence Lab — Self-Regulation Playbook</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --forest: #1A3A1A;
    --mid: #2D5A27;
    --sage: #4A8C3F;
    --mint: #6ECFB5;
    --pale: #EBF5EE;
    --rust: #B85C38;
    --rust-pale: #FDEEE8;
    --navy: #1E3A5F;
    --navy-pale: #EAF0F8;
    --cream: #FAFDF8;
    --dark: #1A2A1A;
    --grey: #5A6A58;
    --light-grey: #888;
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  body {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    background: var(--cream);
    color: var(--dark);
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* ── HERO ── */
  .hero {
    background: var(--forest);
    color: white;
    padding: 60px 40px 50px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: -60px; right: -60px;
    width: 300px; height: 300px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: rgba(110,207,181,0.08);
  }
  .hero::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -40px; left: 60px;
    width: 180px; height: 180px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: rgba(110,207,181,0.05);
  }
  .hero-label {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    color: var(--mint);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 44px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .hero h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--mint);
  }
  .hero p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    max-width: 560px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .hero-tagline {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--mint);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--mint);
    padding-left: 14px;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  /* ── NAV TABS ── */
  .nav {
    background: white;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e0ece0;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(26,58,26,0.06);
  }
  .nav button {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 16px 24px;
    border: none;
    background: none;
    color: var(--grey);
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    border-bottom: 3px solid transparent;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    letter-spacing: 0.3px;
  }
  .nav button:hover { color: var(--sage); }
  .nav button.active {
    color: var(--forest);
    border-bottom-color: var(--mint);
    background: var(--pale);
  }

  /* ── CONTENT ── */
  .content { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 48px 24px 80px; }
  .section { display: none; }
  .section.active { display: block; }

  /* ── SECTION HEADER ── */
  .section-header {
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }
  .section-header .eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mint);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .section-header h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 30px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--forest);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .section-header p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--grey);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  /* ── CARDS ── */
  .card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e0ece0;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .card-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .card-sub {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--grey);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── QUESTION BLOCKS ── */
  .question-block {
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .question-block label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .question-block .q-hint {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--grey);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  textarea {
    width: 100%;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--dark);
    border: 1.5px solid #d0e8d0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    resize: vertical;
    min-height: 80px;
    background: var(--pale);
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  textarea:focus {
    outline: none;
    border-color: var(--mint);
    background: white;
  }
  textarea::placeholder { color: #aac5aa; }

  /* ── ZONE BANDS ── */
  .zone {
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .zone-hyper { background: var(--rust-pale); border-left: 4px solid var(--rust); }
  .zone-window { background: var(--pale); border-left: 4px solid var(--sage); }
  .zone-hypo { background: var(--navy-pale); border-left: 4px solid var(--navy); }
  .zone-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .zone-hyper .zone-label { color: var(--rust); }
  .zone-window .zone-label { color: var(--sage); }
  .zone-hypo .zone-label { color: var(--navy); }
  .zone h3 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .zone-hyper h3 { color: #8B3A1F; }
  .zone-window h3 { color: var(--forest); }
  .zone-hypo h3 { color: var(--navy); }

  /* ── ARCHETYPE SELECTOR ── */
  .archetype-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) { .archetype-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .archetype-btn {
    border: 2px solid #d0e8d0;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 18px 20px;
    cursor: pointer;
    background: white;
    text-align: left;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .archetype-btn:hover { border-color: var(--mint); background: var(--pale); }
  .archetype-btn.selected { border-color: var(--sage); background: var(--pale); }
  .archetype-btn .a-name {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .archetype-btn .a-tag {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--grey);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── 30-DAY PLAN ── */
  .plan-section { display: none; margin-top: 28px; }
  .plan-section.visible { display: block; }

  .week-block {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e0ece0;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .week-header {
    background: var(--forest);
    color: white;
    padding: 14px 24px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .week-header h3 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .week-header .week-theme {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--mint);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .week-body { padding: 20px 24px; }
  .day-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 10px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f7f0;
  }
  .day-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .day-num {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--mint);
    min-width: 36px;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }
  .day-content { flex: 1; }
  .day-title {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .day-body {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--grey);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .day-check {
    width: 20px; height: 20px;
    border: 2px solid #d0e8d0;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    appearance: none;
  }
  .day-check:checked {
    background: var(--sage);
    border-color: var(--sage);
    background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 10 8' fill='none' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cpath d='M1 4l3 3 5-6' stroke='white' stroke-width='1.5' stroke-linecap='round' stroke-linejoin='round'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: center;
    background-size: 10px;
  }

  /* ── RESOURCE LINKS ── */
  .resource-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .resource-card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e0ece0;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 18px 20px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    display: block;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .resource-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--mint);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(26,58,26,0.08);
  }
  .resource-card .r-type {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mint);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .resource-card .r-title {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
  .resource-card .r-desc {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--grey);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .resource-card .r-arrow {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--mint);
    margin-top: 10px;
    display: block;
  }

  /* ── MANTRA DISPLAY ── */
  .mantra-box {
    background: var(--forest);
    color: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .mantra-box .m-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mint);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .mantra-box .m-text {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 3.5vw, 26px);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* ── COMMITMENT CARD ── */
  .commit-card {
    background: var(--forest);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-top: 32px;
    color: white;
  }
  .commit-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .commit-card p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .commit-card label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--mint);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    margin-top: 18px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .commit-card textarea {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    border-color: rgba(110,207,181,0.3);
    color: white;
    min-height: 60px;
  }
  .commit-card textarea::placeholder { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3); }
  .commit-card textarea:focus {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
    border-color: var(--mint);
  }

  /* ── PRINT BUTTON ── */
  .btn-print {
    background: var(--sage);
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin-top: 24px;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .btn-print:hover { background: var(--mid); }

  /* ── DIVIDER ── */
  .divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: #e0ece0;
    margin: 32px 0;
  }

  /* ── PILL ── */
  .pill {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--pale);
    color: var(--sage);
    border: 1px solid #c0e0c0;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    margin-right: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  /* ── FOOTER ── */
  .footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 32px 24px;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--light-grey);
    border-top: 1px solid #e0ece0;
  }

  @media print {
    .nav, .btn-print { display: none; }
    .section { display: block !important; }
    .hero { print-color-adjust: exact; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- HERO -->
<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-label">The Influence Lab · Manchester Metropolitan University</div>
  <h1>Self-Regulation<br><em>Playbook</em></h1>
  <p>Your personal companion for the work that begins after the session. Use this to map your pattern, work through the exercises, and build a regulation practice that actually fits your life.</p>
  <div class="hero-tagline">You cannot regulate others from a place you have not visited in yourself.</div>
</div>

<!-- NAV -->
<nav class="nav">
  <button class="active" onclick="showTab('exercise')">The Exercise</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('archetype')">My Archetype</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('plan')">30-Day Plan</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('resources')">Resources</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('commitment')">My Commitment</button>
</nav>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 1 — THE EXERCISE -->
<div class="content">
<div id="exercise" class="section active">

  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">The Exercise</div>
    <h2>Your Window of Tolerance</h2>
    <p>Using your report as a guide, map your own pattern across all three zones. Write in your own words — not the theory, your lived experience. Then check: does what you have written match what your archetype says about you?</p>
  </div>

  <!-- HYPERAROUSAL -->
  <div class="zone zone-hyper">
    <div class="zone-label">Hyperarousal</div>
    <h3>When I tip into too much</h3>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>What do you do, feel or say when pressure takes you upward?</label>
      <div class="q-hint">Think about the tells — in your body, your behaviour, your relationships. What do people notice? What do you notice, if you stop to look?</div>
      <textarea placeholder="In my body I notice... At work I tend to... The people around me experience..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>What is the earliest signal — the thing that appears just before the pattern kicks in?</label>
      <div class="q-hint">Not the full pattern — the first hint. A tightening, a thought, a behaviour that arrives before you notice you have left the window.</div>
      <textarea placeholder="The earliest signal for me is..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- WINDOW -->
  <div class="zone zone-window">
    <div class="zone-label">Window of Tolerance</div>
    <h3>When I am present and connected, I...</h3>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>What does regulated look like for you specifically?</label>
      <div class="q-hint">Not in theory — in your actual life and work. How do you know when you are in it? What are you doing, feeling, saying?</div>
      <textarea placeholder="When I am in my window I... My leadership feels... My relationships feel..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>What brings you back into the window when you have left it?</label>
      <div class="q-hint">The things that work — not the things you think should work. Be honest about what actually shifts something.</div>
      <textarea placeholder="What genuinely helps me return is..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HYPOAROUSAL -->
  <div class="zone zone-hypo">
    <div class="zone-label">Hypoarousal</div>
    <h3>When I tip into shutdown</h3>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>What does your shutdown look like?</label>
      <div class="q-hint">What do others notice? What do you stop doing, feeling or saying? How does it show up at work, at home, in your relationships?</div>
      <textarea placeholder="When I shut down I... Others tend to notice... At home it looks like..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>What has the shutdown been protecting you from?</label>
      <div class="q-hint">This is a harder question. Sit with it. There is no wrong answer.</div>
      <textarea placeholder="I think my shutdown protects me from..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">Now look at your report</div>
    <div class="card-sub">The moment of recognition</div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>Where does what you wrote match what your archetype says about you?</label>
      <textarea placeholder="What matched was..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>Where did it surprise you?</label>
      <div class="q-hint">The surprises are the most important data. They are the edges of your self-awareness — and the beginning of the work.</div>
      <textarea placeholder="What surprised me was..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>The one thing you know about yourself now that you did not name clearly before today...</label>
      <textarea placeholder="What I now know is..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 2 — MY ARCHETYPE -->
<div id="archetype" class="section">

  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">My Archetype</div>
    <h2>Your Pattern, Your Practice</h2>
    <p>Select your archetype to see your regulation practice — the movement, breath and reframe that works specifically for your pattern.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="archetype-grid">
    <button class="archetype-btn" onclick="selectArchetype('navigator')">
      <div class="a-name">The Navigator</div>
      <div class="a-tag">Momentum as a method of coping</div>
    </button>
    <button class="archetype-btn" onclick="selectArchetype('anchor')">
      <div class="a-name">The Anchor</div>
      <div class="a-tag">Stillness mistaken for strength</div>
    </button>
    <button class="archetype-btn" onclick="selectArchetype('architect')">
      <div class="a-name">The Architect</div>
      <div class="a-tag">Logic as emotional architecture</div>
    </button>
    <button class="archetype-btn" onclick="selectArchetype('connector')">
      <div class="a-name">The Connector</div>
      <div class="a-tag">Attuned to everyone — except themselves</div>
    </button>
  </div>

  <!-- NAVIGATOR -->
  <div id="arch-navigator" class="plan-section">
    <div class="mantra-box">
      <div class="m-label">Your Mantra</div>
      <div class="m-text">"I lead from presence, not pace."</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;margin-bottom:24px;">
      <div class="zone zone-hyper" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Movement</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;">Somatic shake — hands to shoulders, 60 seconds. Let the body move without purpose or direction. Body before mind.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="zone zone-window" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Breath</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;">Vortex breath — inhale slowly through the nose in a widening spiral, hold briefly, exhale as the spiral contracts. Three rounds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="zone zone-hypo" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Reframe</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;font-style:italic;">"What am I moving away from right now?" Name it. One word is enough. Then choose — consciously — what comes next.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">The Navigator's signal</div>
      <div class="card-sub">When the doing accelerates — pause before the next thing</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--grey);line-height:1.7;">You are someone who moves through the world with clarity, direction and a strong drive for progress. This makes you exceptional in leadership. It also means that slowing down — pausing to notice what is happening inside — can feel counterintuitive, even uncomfortable. The pace that looks like ambition is sometimes, at least in part, a way of staying one step ahead of the feelings that stillness might surface. Your practice is the pause before the next thing — not stopping, but choosing.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ANCHOR -->
  <div id="arch-anchor" class="plan-section">
    <div class="mantra-box">
      <div class="m-label">Your Mantra</div>
      <div class="m-text">"I give generously. I include myself."</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;margin-bottom:24px;">
      <div class="zone zone-hyper" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Movement</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;">Somatic shake — hands to shoulders, 60 seconds. The Anchor needs to move what they have been holding still. Let the body release what the mind has been managing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="zone zone-window" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Breath</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;">Two slow inhales through the nose — the second one longer, filling the lungs completely. One long exhale through the mouth. Then one vortex breath. Three rounds total.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="zone zone-hypo" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Reframe</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;font-style:italic;">"What am I carrying right now that is not mine to carry?" Name it. One word. Put it down — even briefly, even symbolically.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">The Anchor's signal</div>
      <div class="card-sub">When the flatness arrives — breathe before you absorb one more thing</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--grey);line-height:1.7;">You have become extraordinarily skilled at absorbing the emotional weight of others. Calm, reliable and present — you are the person people turn to when things are hard. But this steadiness can come at a significant personal cost. When the flatness arrives — the quiet numbness you have learned to call fine — that is your signal. Not to push through. To stop and breathe before you absorb one more thing.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ARCHITECT -->
  <div id="arch-architect" class="plan-section">
    <div class="mantra-box">
      <div class="m-label">Your Mantra</div>
      <div class="m-text">"I do not need to understand it to move through it."</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;margin-bottom:24px;">
      <div class="zone zone-hyper" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Movement</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;">Feet flat on the floor — press them down deliberately. Feel the ground. Then somatic shake, 60 seconds. Let it be unstructured. Let it be slightly uncomfortable. That discomfort is the practice.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="zone zone-window" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Breath</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;">One vortex breath — spiral in slowly through the nose, hold at the top, spiral out through the mouth. Before the next framework, before the next plan. Body first.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="zone zone-hypo" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Reframe</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;font-style:italic;">"What is actually here, underneath the framework?" Not what does this mean. What does this feel like. One word. Not an analysis.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">The Architect's signal</div>
      <div class="card-sub">When analysis accelerates — feel before you frame</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--grey);line-height:1.7;">You find coherence through systems, frameworks and intellectual mastery. This is a formidable quality — but can function as a sophisticated form of emotional avoidance. When uncertainty arises, you potentially reach for analysis rather than attunement. The practice is not eliminating the frameworks. It is feeling what is underneath them before you build them. One word. One feeling. That is enough.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CONNECTOR -->
  <div id="arch-connector" class="plan-section">
    <div class="mantra-box">
      <div class="m-label">Your Mantra</div>
      <div class="m-text">"My needs belong on the list too."</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;margin-bottom:24px;">
      <div class="zone zone-hyper" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Movement</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;">Somatic shake — 60 seconds. This breaks the habitual attunement to everyone else in the room and lands you back in your own body. The movement comes first, before breath, before the reframe.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="zone zone-window" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Breath</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;">Two vortex breaths. Feel your own breath, your own body, your own internal signal — not the room's. This is the practice of turning the attunement inward.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="zone zone-hypo" style="border-radius:10px;">
        <div class="zone-label">Reframe</div>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#555;line-height:1.6;margin-top:8px;font-style:italic;">"Whose needs am I meeting right now — mine or theirs?" No wrong answer. But the asking is everything.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">The Connector's signal</div>
      <div class="card-sub">When shrinking begins — return to yourself first</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--grey);line-height:1.7;">You are potentially one of the most emotionally intelligent people in the room — and one of the most at risk. Your capacity to read others, hold space and create psychological safety is exceptional. But this attunement is often asymmetric: directed outward with great skill, rarely turned inward with the same generosity. When you notice yourself shrinking — saying yes when you mean no — that is your signal.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

