<!-- SECTION 5 — COMMITMENT -->
<div id="commitment" class="section">

  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">My Commitment to Self</div>
    <h2>The Three Things That Matter</h2>
    <p>Not a plan. Not a list of intentions. Three specific commitments — to your pattern, your practice and your mantra. Written by you, for you, to return to when the insight has faded and the pattern is back.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">01 — My Pattern</div>
    <div class="card-sub">What I now know about how I show up under pressure</div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>I am a...</label>
      <div class="q-hint">Your archetype. In your own words — not the label, what it means for you specifically.</div>
      <textarea rows="2" placeholder="I am someone who..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>Under pressure, my signal is...</label>
      <div class="q-hint">The earliest tell. The thing that appears just before the pattern runs.</div>
      <textarea rows="2" placeholder="The first sign is..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>The person who would most benefit from me catching this signal earlier is...</label>
      <div class="q-hint">You do not have to name them aloud. Just hold them clearly in mind as you write.</div>
      <textarea rows="2" placeholder="The person is..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">02 — My Practice</div>
    <div class="card-sub">One thing. Consistent. Small enough to survive the hardest days.</div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>My one regulation practice is...</label>
      <div class="q-hint">Specific enough that you will know whether you did it or not. Not a category — the actual practice.</div>
      <textarea rows="2" placeholder="Every day, I will..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>I will do this when...</label>
      <div class="q-hint">The trigger. The existing moment in the day it attaches to. What happens just before?</div>
      <textarea rows="2" placeholder="The trigger is..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>My reframe question is...</label>
      <div class="q-hint">The question you will ask yourself when the signal arrives. From your archetype practice.</div>
      <textarea rows="2" placeholder="I will ask myself..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">03 — My Mantra</div>
    <div class="card-sub">The sentence you will return to when the pattern kicks in</div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>My mantra is...</label>
      <div class="q-hint">From your archetype slide — or written in your own words if something else fits better. Short enough to say in a breath.</div>
      <textarea rows="2" placeholder="My mantra is..."></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="question-block">
      <label>In 30 days, I want to notice...</label>
      <div class="q-hint">Not a goal. Not a metric. What would be different if the practice is working — in your body, your leadership, your relationships?</div>
      <textarea rows="3" placeholder="In 30 days, I hope to notice..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mantra-box" style="margin-top:32px;">
    <div class="m-label">A Final Note from Kay</div>
    <div class="m-text" style="font-size:18px;margin-bottom:16px;">"You cannot regulate others from a place you have not visited in yourself."</div>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6);line-height:1.7;max-width:520px;margin:0 auto;">The work you did today is real. The insight you have right now is real. The practice is keeping it real when the pressure returns and the pattern offers itself as the easier path. Return to this playbook. Return to the exercise. Return to the commitment. The regulation is in the returning.</p>
    <p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--mint);margin-top:16px;">Kay Littlehales · The Influence Lab · theinfluencelab.com</p>
  </div>

  <button class="btn-print" onclick="window.print()">Save or Print This Playbook</button>

</div>
